	<link href="@Url.Content("~/Content/Normalize.css")" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
	<link href="@Url.Content("~/Content/MainPage.css")" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
	<link href="@Url.Content("~/Content/WebFlow.css")" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
	<script src="@Url.Content("~/Scripts/Services/BlogPostService.js")" type="text/javascript"></script>
	<script src="@Url.Content("~/Scripts/Controllers/BlogPostController.js")" type="text/javascript"></script>
	<script src="@Url.Content("~/Scripts/Controllers/TwitterController.js")" type="text/javascript"></script>
	@RenderSection("headerPlugins", false)
</head>
<body ng-app="theApp">
	<div id="header" class="header">
		<div class="w-container">
			<div class="navigation">
				<a href="#header" class="logo-link w-inline-block">
					<h1 class="logo">Arthur Correa</h1>
				</a>
				<a href="#my-story" class="nav-link">About me</a>
				<a href="#built" class="nav-link">Things I&#x27;ve Built</a>
				<a href="#online" class="nav-link">Recent Blog Entries</a>
				<a href="#" class="nav-link">Contact</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="my-story" class="section">
		<div class="w-container">
			<div class="w-row">
				<div class="align-right w-col w-col-4">
					<h2>About me</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="w-col w-col-8">
					<p>I am a software architect, hockey player,, Disney fan, and family man.</p>
					<p>As a software architecture I&#x27;m a firm believer in modern practices such as Domain Driven Design, Microservices, Containers, CI/CD, Dev Ops and deploying to the cloud. I most enjoy designing and building distributed systems built using microservices, but I&#x27;m not too particular about what technology I use to build them. I have built production systems in Java, .Net/.Net Core, and Node deployed to AWS and Azure, but I'm open to other things as well.</p>
					<p>As a hockey player. I&#x27;ve gone from someone that wants to play as competitively as I can and keep getting better to someone that just does it for fun and exercise. Nowadays I&#x27;m just happy if I can get up and down the ice without looking like an idiot.</p>
					<p>I&#x27;m a big Disney fan. I've loved going to Disney World since I was a kid,, and I never seem to get sick of it. Everything from the theming, to the rides, to the food. Every time I go there I'm trying to soak it all in. My favorite park is probably Magic Kingdom, and my favorite ride is Splash Mountain.</p>
					<p>And the best for last. As a family man I love to spend my time out of work with my family.  Either driving my kids to or from all their sports, playing board games, or going to Disney with them. &#x27;</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="built" class="section grey">
		<div class="w-container">
			<div class="w-row">
				<div class="align-right w-col w-col-4">
					<h2>Things I&#x27;ve Built</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="w-col w-col-8">
					<div class="w-row">
						<div class="w-col w-col-4">
							<div class="white-box">
								<img src="Content/images/noun_Radar_9219.png" srcset="Content/images/noun_Radar_9219-p-500.png 500w, Content/images/noun_Radar_9219.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 27vw, (max-width: 767px) 19vw, (max-width: 991px) 8vw, 61.125px" alt="" class="grid-image">
								<h3>Blog</h3>
								<p>Here I blog about anything on the topics from Programming to Hockey to Disney. I wrote the blog software myself using  C#, .Net, MVC, and Angular. </p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="w-col w-col-4">
							<div class="white-box">
								<img src="Content/images/noun_Radar_9219.png" srcset="Content/images/noun_Radar_9219-p-500.png 500w, Content/images/noun_Radar_9219.png 700w" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 27vw, (max-width: 767px) 19vw, (max-width: 991px) 8vw, 61.125px" alt="" class="grid-image">
								<h3>Technology Radar</h3>
								<p>My personal Technology Radar. The site also lets you manage your own personal Technology Radar once you&#x27;ve logged in with Auth0. I wrote this with Java, Spring Boot, React and Docker.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="w-col w-col-4">
							<div class="white-box">
								<img src="https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/5ab4147a43dc64b2180c31f3/5ab4147a43dc6406fc0c3206_social-01-white.svg" alt="" class="grid-image">
								<h3>Point Chart</h3>
								<p>A site for setting up Point Charts for children.  This was built using C#, .Net, MVC, and React</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="online" class="section">
		<div class="w-container">
			<div class="w-row">
				<div class="align-right w-col w-col-4">
					<h2>Recent Blog Entries</h2>
				</div>
				<a class="w-col w-col-8">
					<a class="col-md-8" ng-controller="BlogPostController" ng-init="getMostRecent('@PucksAndProgramming.MainSite.MvcApplication.BlogUrlRoot')">
						<div ng-show="waitingForData">
							<img src="/Content/Images/waitingForData.gif" /> Loading most recent blog post
						</div>
						<p ng-show="!waitingForData">
							<a href="journal-page.html" class="journal-entry w-inline-block">
								<h2>{{ mostRecentBlogPost.Title }}</h2>
								<p>Posted {{ formatDate(mostRecentBlogPost.DatePosted) | date:"MM/dd/yyyy" }}<p>
								<p ng-bind-html="mostRecentBlogPost.ShortEntryText"></p>
							</a>
						</p>
					</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div id="journal" class="section grey">
		<div class="w-container">
			<div class="w-row">
				<div class="align-right w-col w-col-4">
					<h2>Contact</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="w-col w-col-8">
					<div class="w-form">
						<form name="email-form" data-name="Email Form"><input type="text" name="name" data-name="Name" placeholder="Enter your name" maxlength="256" class="field w-input"><input type="email" name="email" data-name="Email" placeholder="Enter your email address" maxlength="256" required="" class="field w-input"><textarea placeholder="Example Text" maxlength="5000" class="field comments w-input"></textarea><input type="submit" value="Send Message" data-wait="Please wait..." class="button blue w-button"></form>
						<div class="success w-form-done">
							<h2>Thank you!</h2>
							<p>Your submission has been received!</p>
						</div>
						<div class="w-form-fail">
							<p>Oops! Something went wrong while submitting the form :(</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>

